\chapter{World Skills Software Setup Guide}
\label{\detokenize{docs/WorldSkills/setup:world-skills-software-setup-guide}}\label{\detokenize{docs/WorldSkills/setup::doc}}
\begin{sphinxadmonition}{note}{Note:}
This setup is for Java/C++ only
\end{sphinxadmonition}

Windows

\sphinxstylestrong{Online Installer}

\begin{sphinxadmonition}{warning}{Warning:}
Windows 7: You \sphinxstylestrong{must} install the standalone version of .NET Version 4.62+ which can be found \sphinxhref{https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/3151800/the-net-framework-4-6-2-offline-installer-for-windows}{here}.
\end{sphinxadmonition}

Download the installer (32bit or 64bit) \sphinxhref{https://github.com/wpilibsuite/allwpilib/releases}{from WPI}.

\noindent\sphinxincludegraphics{{worldskills-software-setup-1}.PNG}

Installing for \sphinxstyleemphasis{All Users} will require admin privileges and install for all users on the machine.

\begin{sphinxadmonition}{note}{Note:}
Software will be installed to \sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{C:\textbackslash{}Users\textbackslash{}Public\textbackslash{}wpilib\textbackslash{}YYYY}}. YYYY Corresponds to the currently suppored year.
\end{sphinxadmonition}

\sphinxstylestrong{Download VS Code}
\begin{quote}

Due to licensing reasons with VS Code the installer does not contain it bundled in. To overcome this hit the \sphinxstyleemphasis{Select/Download VS Code} button.

\noindent\sphinxincludegraphics{{worldskills-software-setup-2}.PNG}

This will open up the selector tool.

\noindent\sphinxincludegraphics{{worldskills-software-setup-3}.PNG}

Select the \sphinxstyleemphasis{Download} option and VS Code will be downloaded.

\noindent\sphinxincludegraphics{{worldskills-software-setup-4}.PNG}

Once VS Code is downloaded the window will auto change back to the installer window and \sphinxstyleemphasis{Execute Install} can be run.

\noindent\sphinxincludegraphics{{worldskills-software-setup-5}.PNG}
\end{quote}

\sphinxstylestrong{What was just Installed}
\begin{quote}
\begin{itemize}
\item {} 
\sphinxstyleemphasis{Visual Stuido Code} \sphinxhyphen{} The prefered and suppored IDE for robot code development.

\item {} 
\sphinxstyleemphasis{C++ Compiler} \sphinxhyphen{} Toolchains required for building C++ code.

\item {} 
\sphinxstyleemphasis{Java JDK/JRE} \sphinxhyphen{} Specific version of the JDK/JRE that is used to build code.

\item {} 
\sphinxstyleemphasis{Gradle} \sphinxhyphen{} Specific version of Gradle used for building and deploying Java or C++ code to the VMXpi

\item {} 
\sphinxstyleemphasis{WPILib Tools} \sphinxhyphen{} Tools used for robot enhancement

\item {} 
\sphinxstyleemphasis{WPILib Dependencies} \sphinxhyphen{} OpenCV, etc.

\item {} 
\sphinxstyleemphasis{VS Code Extensions} \sphinxhyphen{} WPILib extensions for robot code development

\end{itemize}

\begin{sphinxadmonition}{important}{Important:}
The installer creates a seperate version of VS Code for robotics development, even if VS Code is already installed locally. This is done to prevent workflows from breaking.
\end{sphinxadmonition}
\end{quote}

\sphinxstylestrong{Offline Installer}

\begin{sphinxadmonition}{warning}{Warning:}
Windows 7: You \sphinxstylestrong{must} install the standalone version of .NET Version 4.62+ which can be found \sphinxhref{https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/3151800/the-net-framework-4-6-2-offline-installer-for-windows}{here}. Before preceding!
\end{sphinxadmonition}

The offline installation files will be located in the USB provided inside the collection. Locate and run the file named \sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{WPILibInstaller\_Windows64\sphinxhyphen{}2020.3.2.exe}} or \sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{WPILibInstaller\_Windows32\sphinxhyphen{}2020.3.2.exe}} based on your OS.

\noindent\sphinxincludegraphics{{worldskills-software-setup-1}.PNG}

Installing for \sphinxstyleemphasis{All Users} will require admin privileges and install for all users on the machine.

\begin{sphinxadmonition}{note}{Note:}
Software will be installed to \sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{C:\textbackslash{}Users\textbackslash{}Public\textbackslash{}wpilib\textbackslash{}YYYY}}. YYYY Corresponds to the currently suppored year.
\end{sphinxadmonition}

\sphinxstylestrong{Download VS Code}
\begin{quote}

Due to licensing reasons with VS Code the installer does not contain it bundled in. To overcome this hit the \sphinxstyleemphasis{Select/Download VS Code} button.

\noindent\sphinxincludegraphics{{worldskills-software-setup-2}.PNG}

This will open up the selector tool.

\noindent\sphinxincludegraphics{{worldskills-software-setup-3}.PNG}

Select the \sphinxstyleemphasis{Select Existing Download} option and then select the file \sphinxcode{\sphinxupquote{OfflineVsCodeFiles\sphinxhyphen{}1.41.1.zip}}. This will change back to the installer window and \sphinxstyleemphasis{Execute Install} can be run.

\noindent\sphinxincludegraphics{{worldskills-software-setup-5}.PNG}
\end{quote}

\sphinxstylestrong{What was just Installed}
\begin{quote}
\begin{itemize}
\item {} 
\sphinxstyleemphasis{Visual Stuido Code} \sphinxhyphen{} The prefered and suppored IDE for robot code development.

\item {} 
\sphinxstyleemphasis{C++ Compiler} \sphinxhyphen{} Toolchains required for building C++ code.

\item {} 
\sphinxstyleemphasis{Java JDK/JRE} \sphinxhyphen{} Specific version of the JDK/JRE that is used to build code.

\item {} 
\sphinxstyleemphasis{Gradle} \sphinxhyphen{} Specific version of Gradle used for building and deploying Java or C++ code to the VMXpi

\item {} 
\sphinxstyleemphasis{WPILib Tools} \sphinxhyphen{} Tools used for robot enhancement

\item {} 
\sphinxstyleemphasis{WPILib Dependencies} \sphinxhyphen{} OpenCV, etc.

\item {} 
\sphinxstyleemphasis{VS Code Extensions} \sphinxhyphen{} WPILib extensions for robot code development

\end{itemize}

\begin{sphinxadmonition}{important}{Important:}
The installer creates a seperate version of VS Code for robotics development, even if VS Code is already installed locally. This is done to prevent workflows from breaking.
\end{sphinxadmonition}
\end{quote}
